 105:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****  *
 106:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c **** @verbatim
 107:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****  ===============================================================================
 108:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****               ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
 109:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****  ===============================================================================
 110:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****     [..]  This section provides functions allowing to:
 111:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****       (+) Initialize the Flash interface, the NVIC allocation and initial time base
 112:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****           clock configuration.
 113:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****       (+) De-initialize common part of the HAL.
 114:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****       (+) Configure the time base source to have 1ms time base with a dedicated
 115:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****           Tick interrupt priority.
 116:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****         (++) SysTick timer is used by default as source of time base, but user
 117:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              can eventually implement his proper time base source (a general purpose
 118:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              timer for example or other time source), keeping in mind that Time base
 119:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              duration should be kept 1ms since PPP_TIMEOUT_VALUEs are defined and
 120:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              handled in milliseconds basis.
 121:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****         (++) Time base configuration function (HAL_InitTick ()) is called automatically
 122:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              at the beginning of the program after reset by HAL_Init() or at any time
 123:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              when clock is configured, by HAL_RCC_ClockConfig().
 124:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****         (++) Source of time base is configured  to generate interrupts at regular
 125:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              time intervals. Care must be taken if HAL_Delay() is called from a
 126:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              peripheral ISR process, the Tick interrupt line must have higher priority
 127:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****             (numerically lower) than the peripheral interrupt. Otherwise the caller
 128:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****             ISR process will be blocked.
 129:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****        (++) functions affecting time base configurations are declared as __weak
 130:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****              to make  override possible  in case of other  implementations in user file.
 131:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c **** @endverbatim
 132:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal.c ****   * @{
